    <section>
      <title>Section 4.1:
        Matrices and Multiplication (MX1) </title>
      <slide>
        <title>Observation 4.1.1 </title>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-b-a-a">
If <m original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-b-a-a-a">T: \IR^n \rightarrow \IR^m</m> and <m original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-b-a-a-b">S: \IR^m \rightarrow \IR^k</m> are linear maps,
then the composition map <m original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1m3" internal-id="m-MX1-c-b-a-a-c">S\circ T</m>
computed as <m original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1m4" internal-id="m-MX1-c-b-a-a-d"> (S \circ T)(\vec{v})=S(T(\vec{v}))</m>
is a linear map from <m original-id="MX1-s3o2s1p1m5" internal-id="m-MX1-c-b-a-a-e">\IR^n \rightarrow \IR^k</m>.
        </p>
        <figure original-id="MX1-s3o2s1f2" internal-id="figure-MX1-c-b-a-b">
          <image source="generated/latex-image/MX1-image-composition.svg"/>
          <caption original-id="MX1-s3o2s1f2c2" internal-id="caption-MX1-c-b-a-b-b">The composition of two linear maps.</caption>
        </figure>
      </slide>
      <slide>
        <title>Activity 4.1.1 (~20 min)</title>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-a-a">
Let <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-a">T: \IR^3 \rightarrow \IR^2</m> be defined by
the <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-b">2\times 3</m> starndard matrix <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m3" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-c">B</m> and
<m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m4" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-d">S: \IR^2 \rightarrow \IR^4</m> be defined by the
<m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m5" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-e">4\times 2</m> standard matrix <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m6" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-f">A</m>:
<me original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m7" internal-id="me-MX1-c-c-a-a-g">B=\left[\begin{array}{ccc} 2 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\ 5 &amp; -3 &amp; 4 \end{array}\right]
    \hspace{2em}
A=\left[\begin{array}{cc} 1 &amp; 2 \\ 0 &amp; 1 \\ 3 &amp; 5 \\ -1 &amp; -2 \end{array}\right]</me>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>Part 1.</em>
        </p>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t2p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-b-a">
What are the domain and codomain of the composition map <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-a-a">S \circ T</m>?
        </p>
        <ol marker="A." cols="2" original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2" internal-id="ol-MX1-c-c-b-b">
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l1" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-b-b-a">
            <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l1p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-b-b-a-a"> The domain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l1p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-a-a-a">\IR ^3</m> and the codomain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l1p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-a-a-b">\IR^2</m>
</p>
          </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l2" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-b-b-b">
            <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l2p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-b-b-b-a"> The domain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l2p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-b-a-a">\IR ^2</m> and the codomain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l2p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-b-a-b">\IR^4</m>
</p>
          </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l3" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-b-b-c">
            <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l3p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-b-b-c-a"> The domain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l3p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-c-a-a">\IR ^3</m> and the codomain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l3p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-c-a-b">\IR^4</m>
</p>
          </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l4" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-b-b-d">
            <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l4p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-b-b-d-a"> The domain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l4p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-d-a-a">\IR ^4</m> and the codomain is <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t2o2l4p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-b-b-d-a-b">\IR^3</m>
</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </slide>
      <slide>
        <title>Activity 4.1.1 (~20 min)</title>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-a-a">
Let <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-a">T: \IR^3 \rightarrow \IR^2</m> be defined by
the <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-b">2\times 3</m> starndard matrix <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m3" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-c">B</m> and
<m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m4" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-d">S: \IR^2 \rightarrow \IR^4</m> be defined by the
<m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m5" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-e">4\times 2</m> standard matrix <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m6" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-f">A</m>:
<me original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m7" internal-id="me-MX1-c-c-a-a-g">B=\left[\begin{array}{ccc} 2 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\ 5 &amp; -3 &amp; 4 \end{array}\right]
    \hspace{2em}
A=\left[\begin{array}{cc} 1 &amp; 2 \\ 0 &amp; 1 \\ 3 &amp; 5 \\ -1 &amp; -2 \end{array}\right]</me>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>Part 2.</em>
        </p>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3a3t3p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-c-a">
        What size will the standard matrix of <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t3p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-c-a-a">S \circ T</m> be?
                </p>
        <ol marker="A." cols="2" original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2" internal-id="ol-MX1-c-c-c-b">
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l1" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-c-b-a"> <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-c-b-a-a">4 \text{ (rows)} \times 3 \text{ (columns)}</m>
        </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l2" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-c-b-b"> <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l2m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-c-b-b-a">3 \text{ (rows)} \times 4 \text{ (columns)}</m>
        </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l3" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-c-b-c"> <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l3m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-c-b-c-a">3 \text{ (rows)} \times 2 \text{ (columns)}</m>
        </li>
          <li original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l4" internal-id="li-MX1-c-c-c-b-d"> <m original-id="MX1-s3a3t3o2l4m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-c-b-d-a">2 \text{ (rows)} \times 4 \text{ (columns)}</m>
        </li>
        </ol>
      </slide>
      <slide>
        <title>Activity 4.1.1 (~20 min)</title>
        <p original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1" internal-id="p-MX1-c-c-a-a">
Let <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m1" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-a">T: \IR^3 \rightarrow \IR^2</m> be defined by
the <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m2" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-b">2\times 3</m> starndard matrix <m original-id="MX1-s3a3i1p1m3" internal-id="m-MX1-c-c-a-a-c">B</m> and
